Logistic Regression with PyMC3¶

In [5]:
# data preparation 
m = len(exog)
x = df[exog].values
y = df[endog].values
x_shared = theano.shared(x)

# sampling parameters 
nIter = 500
nBurn = 1000
chains = 4
cores = 2
randomSeed = 1123890

with pm.Model() as model:
    coeff = pm.Normal('beta', mu=0, sigma=100,shape=m)
    line = tt.sum(coeff * x_shared, axis=1)
    logistic = pm.math.sigmoid( line )
    pm.Bernoulli('obs', p=logistic, observed=y)

    # fit the model
    trace = pm.sample(draws=nIter,
                      tune=nBurn, 
                      chains=chains,
                      cores=cores,
                      random_seed=randomSeed)

Logistic Regression with PyMC3 using custom function¶

If you want to use Class for calculation of likelihood with NUTS or Hamiltonian MC,
it's very heavy task because you should define likelihood and gradient by your self.
See https://docs.pymc.io/notebooks/blackbox_external_likelihood.html .
However, we can easily implement likelihood and make use of NUTS or Hamiltonian MC,
using "function only", because "autograd" module automatically calculates your likelihood,
(given that you only use simple calculation syntax and numpy module. )

In [13]:
EPS = np.finfo(float).eps
def logiFunc(x):
    v = 1./(1. + tt.exp(-x) )
    v = tt.clip(v,EPS,1-EPS)
    return(v)
 
def pred(X,w):
    linear = tt.sum(w*X,axis=1)
    y =  logiFunc(linear)  
    return(y)

def logLikelihood(t,X,w):
    y = pred(X,w) 
    ll = t * tt.log(y) + (1-t)*tt.log(1-y) 
    ll = tt.sum(ll)
    return(ll)

# sampling parameters 

nIter = 500
with pm.Model() as model2:
    coeff = pm.Normal('beta', mu=0, sigma=100,shape=m)
    pm.DensityDist('likelihood',logLikelihood , observed=dict(t=y,X=x,w=coeff))

    # fit the model
    trace2 = pm.sample(draws=nIter)

Record reuslts of PyMC3¶

data are saved using pickle.

In [16]:
import pickle
import datetime
In [17]:
# data preparation 
df = sm.datasets.anes96.load_pandas().data
exog = ["TVnews","selfLR","PID","educ"]
endog = "vote"

# set data 
m = len(exog)
x = df[exog].values
y = df[endog].values
x_shared = theano.shared(x)

# sampling parameters 
nIter = 500

with pm.Model() as model3:
    coeff = pm.Normal('beta', mu=0, sigma=100,shape=m)
    line = tt.sum(coeff * x_shared, axis=1)
    logistic = pm.math.sigmoid( line )
    pm.Bernoulli('obs', p=logistic, observed=y)

    # fit the model
    trace3 = pm.sample(draws=nIter)
# save result using pickle.
time = datetime.datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d%H%M")
savePath = "./model_%s.db" % time 

with open(savePath, 'wb') as buff:
    pickle.dump({'model': model3, 'trace': trace3, 'x_shared': x_shared}, buff)
